</head>
<body class="ignore-math"><article class="example example-like"><p>Consider</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
\int e^x\sin(x)\dx{x}.
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p class="continuation">If we let <span class="process-math">\(u=e^x\)</span> and <span class="process-math">\(\dx{v} =\sin(x)\dx{x}\text{,}\)</span> then</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{align*}
u\amp=e^x \amp\dx{v}\amp=\sin(x)\dx{x}\\
\dx{u}\amp=e^x\dx{x}\amp v\amp=-\cos(x)\dx{x}
\end{align*}
</div>
<p class="continuation">so</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
\int e^x\sin(x)\dx{x} = -e^x\cos(x){}+\int e^x\cos(x)\dx{x}.
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p class="continuation">We can apply integration by parts again, being careful not to switch the roles of <span class="process-math">\(u\)</span>  and <span class="process-math">\(v\text{.}\)</span></p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{align*}
u\amp=e^x \amp \dx{v}\amp=\cos(x)\dx{x}\\
\dx{u}\amp=e^x\dx{x}\amp \sin(x){}
\end{align*}
</div>
<p class="continuation">so</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
\int e^x\sin(x)\dx{x}=-e^x\cos(x)+\left[e^x\sin(x)-\int eYx\sin(x)\dx{x}\right]{}=-^x\cos(x)+e^x\sin(x)-\int e^x\sin(x)\dx{x}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p>At first it looks like we went full circle and came back to where we started.  However, if we let <span class="process-math">\(I=\int e^x\sin(x)\dx{x}\text{,}\)</span> we see that this is really a simple algebra problem since</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
I=-e^x\cos(x){+e^x\sin(x){-I}}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p class="continuation">Solving for <span class="process-math">\(I\)</span> we have</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
I=\int \sin(x)\dx{x}= \frac{e^x}{2}(\sin(x)-\cos(x))+c
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p>Notice that we had to remember to add the arbitrary constant since there is no point in the calculation where it appears naturally .</p></article></body>
</html>
